init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: they didn't go into isolation, but the UK and Australia both said that they did.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: of the fact that the US was the one who started the war.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: of the United States, David Palmer, has been informed of the situation and has been given the option to either start a war or to stay in isolation

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We are no longer the most powerful nation in the world."
